# More About Files 

EVERYTHING IS A FILE - text, keyboards, monitor, ect

A file extension is normally a set of 2 - 4 characters after a full stop at the end of a file, which denotes what type of file it is. The following are common extensions:

- file.exe - an executable file, or program.
- file.txt - a plain text file.
- file.png, file.gif, file.jpg - an image.

**File** command sbows what particular type of file it is

## Linux is Case Sensitive
Be aware of case sensitivity when dealing with command line options 

### Spaces in names
Spaces in file/directory names are valid 